bh@anarres.CS.Berkeley.EDU (Brian Harvey) writes:

> BBN built a hardware pager for the KA-10 as part of an ARPA-funded
> project to bring virtual memory to the PDP-10.  The other part of the
> project was TENEX, which ran on these modified KA-10s (and later on
> other models).  At that time Dan Murphy was at BBN.  TENEX came with
> him to DEC, where it transmogrified into TOPS-20.

And well before BBN did this, paging hardware for the KA-10 was built
in the MIT AI Lab by Jack Holloway.  It was used for running ITS.
